CRITICAL: Command Center disk usage is in the danger zone

{{ notification.body }}

This affects every organization on this Command Center, not just yours.
When the disk fills:
  - SQLite writes start failing — recordings, audit logs, motion events
    stop persisting silently.
  - The dashboard will continue serving live HLS streams (those are
    in-memory) but everything that touches the database breaks.

What to do RIGHT NOW:
  1. Open the admin health page: {{ dashboard_url }}/admin/health
  2. Check the disk usage stats and recent log volume.
  3. Either resize the Fly volume (`fly volumes extend ...`) or run
     log retention cleanup if the volume is full of old logs.

Don't wait for the next email. Each follow-up alert is gated for 6 hours,
so if you get a second one, the first didn't fix anything.

